<li class="commentbody" id="comment-505942">
			<cite><a href='http://www.sycamorestirrings.blogspot.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>katy</a></cite>
						&nbsp;
			<a class="commentlink" href="#comment-505942" title="">December 23, 2010</a> 

		
			<div class="commentcount">14</div>

				<p>okay, i&#8217;m about to blow your mind, not that I like to toot my own horn or anything.  I use MS&#8217;s recipe every year for gingerbread.  This year I used treacle instead of molasses (I live in Europe and molasses is hard to come by) and whoa.  Total flavor enhancer.  TOTAL.  It makes the cookie so much richer.  I didn&#8217;t even use the black pepper because I was out.  Treacle is amazing.  You have not tasted gingerbread cookies until you have used treacle.  Give it a try next year and see what you think.  I thought it would just be a simple substitution.  Wrong.  Adds a wonderful flavor.  Merry Christmas. xo</p>
	</li>
		
		
		
	
