				<p>I made gingerbread from a Martha Stewart Living magazine recipe years ago and I&#8217;ve been searching for it ever since. The gingerbread had a tablespoon or so of bacon grease in the recipe. It gave the gingerbread the most wonderful hint of smokiness that went perfectly with the ginger. If anyone still has that bacony gingerbread recipe, I&#8217;d sure love to have it. Also, find a spectacular lemon curd (like Trader Joe&#8217;s) and dip your gingerbread cookies! Yum!</p>
